From: bluecat <lmhtq1991@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 28 May 2026 11:30:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] Phase C-6 fix #5: skip generate_string_indexof_stubs on CHERI

Pinpointed via dladdr + addr2line on __builtin_return_address(0..3)
from inside the assembler_aarch64.hpp f() guarantee. The
`MacroAssembler::sub(Reg, Reg, uint64_t)` call from
`generate_string_indexof_linear` produces an immediate too big for
the 12-bit add/sub-imm field; `wrap_adds_subs_imm_insn` falls back to
`mov(Rd, imm) + sub-reg`; the `mov` path encodes via bfm-family
logical-immediate, whose `imms` field at bits [15:10] is only 6 bits
and overflows for the generated constant (val=64, nbits=6).

Crash trace at the moment of the guarantee:
  ra1 = MacroAssembler::sub(Reg, Reg, unsigned long)
        macroAssembler_aarch64.hpp:1187
  ra2 = StubGenerator::generate_string_indexof_stubs
        stubGenerator_aarch64.cpp:5703
  ra3 = StubGenerator constructor

v1 fix: under __CHERI_PURE_CAPABILITY__, skip the three
generate_string_indexof_linear calls and leave the stub pointers as
nullptr. The JIT/interpreter falls back to the plain-Java
String.indexOf implementation. Correct but unoptimized.

v2 future fix (not yet done): make mov(Rd, imm) purecap-aware so it
chooses an encoding whose imms field doesn't overflow.

Validated: with this patch, `java -XX:+UseStoplessGC -version`
proceeds past stubRoutines_init2 + MethodHandles::generate_adapters
and reaches initialize_java_lang_classes (the first Java method
execution). Next blocker is a hang inside `String::<clinit>` — see
docs/24_c6_breakthrough_to_string_clinit.md.

diff --git a/src/hotspot/cpu/aarch64/stubGenerator_aarch64.cpp b/src/hotspot/cpu/aarch64/stubGenerator_aarch64.cpp
--- a/src/hotspot/cpu/aarch64/stubGenerator_aarch64.cpp
+++ b/src/hotspot/cpu/aarch64/stubGenerator_aarch64.cpp
@@ -5700,9 +5700,21 @@
   }

   void generate_string_indexof_stubs() {
+#ifdef __CHERI_PURE_CAPABILITY__
+    // C-6 fix #5: skip string-indexof stub generation on CHERI purecap.
+    // generate_string_indexof_linear emits a sub immediate that
+    // doesn't fit the 12-bit add/sub field, so wrap_adds_subs_imm_insn
+    // falls back to mov(Rd, imm)+sub-reg, and the mov path trips the
+    // assembler imms-field guarantee (val=64 in a 6-bit field).
+    // Leaving these as nullptr makes the JIT fall back to the Java
+    // String.indexOf implementation — correct but unoptimized.
+    StubRoutines::aarch64::_string_indexof_linear_ll = nullptr;
+    StubRoutines::aarch64::_string_indexof_linear_uu = nullptr;
+    StubRoutines::aarch64::_string_indexof_linear_ul = nullptr;
+#else
     StubRoutines::aarch64::_string_indexof_linear_ll = generate_string_indexof_linear(true, true);
     StubRoutines::aarch64::_string_indexof_linear_uu = generate_string_indexof_linear(false, false);
     StubRoutines::aarch64::_string_indexof_linear_ul = generate_string_indexof_linear(true, false);
+#endif
   }

   void inflate_and_store_2_fp_registers(bool generatePrfm,
